We present the results of a search for the rare decays $B	o h
u\overline{
u}$, where $h$ stands for $K^+,\:K^0_{\mathrm{S}},\:K^{\ast +},\:K^{\ast 0},\:\pi^+,\:\pi^0,\:ho^+$ and $ho^{0}$. The results are obtained with $772	imes10^{6}$ $B\overline{B}$ pairs collected with the Belle detector at the KEKB $e^+ e^-$ collider. We reconstruct one $B$ meson in a semileptonic decay and require a single $h$ meson but nothing else on the signal side. We observe no significant signal and set upper limits on the branching fractions. The limits set on the $B	o K^0_{\mathrm{S}}
u\overline{
u}$, $B^0	o K^{*0}
